This paper discusses bibliometric indicators of journal performance, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The Eigenfactor indicator, audience factor, and influence weight indicator are all related to the impact and influence of academic publications, which is relevant to the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of these indicators also involves the use of citation data and network analysis, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of these indicators, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR). Overall, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, and cs.CR.
